Rampla Juniors      1-1 Deportivo Maldonado   [6-5 pen]
  [Raphael Aguerre 81; Mario Barceló 69]
  [Penalties: 1-0 Dardo Pereira, 1-1 Carlos Márcora, 2-1 Gustavo Badell,
     2-2 Milton Cortés, 3-2 Elbio Pappa, 3-3 Aldo Giménez, 4-3 José Batlle Perdomo,
     4-4 Julio Aldao, 5-4 Fernando Kanapkis, 5-5 Marcos Affonso, 6-5 Raphael Aguerre,
     6-5 Pablo Cuello (held)]

Deportivo Maldonado remain in Segunda División Profesional.

However, Deportivo Maldonado were given a license for the Primera División
Profesional after the season, together with Tacuarembó FC and Atlético
Bella Vista (Paysandú).

Since this leaves the second division with 13 teams in 1999, there is
an additional playoff for the 14th place:

First Leg [Mar 6, 1999]
Villa Teresa        1-0 El Tanque Sisley
  [Nogueira 45]

Second Leg [Mar 13, 1999]
El Tanque Sisley    2-1 Villa Teresa
  [Jorge Charquero 14, Carlos Pereyra 65; Richard González 28]

Third Leg [Mar 20, 1999]
El Tanque Sisley    2-1 Villa Teresa
  [Marcelo Durán 10, Marcelo Dopazo 75pen; Richard González 47]

El Tanque Sisley qualified for 1999 second division.

Relegated from first division: Villa Española and Montevideo Wanderers.
Promoted from third division: Cerrito.




Third Level 1998


Liga Metropolitana Amateur

First Phase

First four qualify for second phase.  Second phase consists of a double
round robin, each team starting at zero points.  The winners of the two
phases play off for the championship and promotion to the 2nd division.

