When Deportivo Maldonado were given a license for the Primera División
Profesional after the season, the second division was left with 13 teams
in 1999, therefore an additional playoff for the 14th place is played:

First Leg [Mar 6, 1999]
Villa Teresa        1-0 El Tanque Sisley
  [Nogueira 45]

Second Leg [Mar 13, 1999]
El Tanque Sisley    2-1 Villa Teresa
  [Jorge Charquero 14, Carlos Pereyra 65; Richard González 28]

Third Leg [Mar 20, 1999]
El Tanque Sisley    2-1 Villa Teresa
  [Marcelo Durán 10, Marcelo Dopazo 75pen; Richard González 47]

El Tanque Sisley qualified for 1999 second division.



Futbol del Interior (OFI) 1998
=========================

Torneo de Clubes Campeones de OFI.

(first major tournament of the clubs who won the championships of the
 "interior"; amateur, organized by OFI; 8 teams playing double round
 robin in two groups of 4).

NB: OFI organizes amateur football in 18 of 19 provinces in Uruguay (AUF 
    organizes professional football and amateur football in Montevideo).

    The provinces concerned are:
    Artigas (capital Artigas), Salto (Salto), Paysandú (Paysandú), 
    Río Negro (Fray Bentos), Soriano (Mercedes), Colonia (Colonia),
    San José (San José), Flores (Trinidad), Florida (Florida), 
    Lavalleja (Minas), Canelones (Canelones), Maldonado (Maldonado),
    Rocha (Rocha), Treinta y Tres (Treinta y Tres), Cerro Largo (Melo),
    Durazno (Durazno), Tacuarembó (Tacuarembó), Rivera (Rivera).

    OFI itself consists of three confederations:
    Litoral (Artigas, Salto, Paysandú, Río Negro, Tacuarembó, Rivera,
             Soriano and Colonia Interior (province without capital);
    Sur (Colonia Capital, San José, Flores, Florida, Durazno, Canelones
         [southern, northern and western part], Paso de los Toros [city
         in the south of Tacuarembó]);
    Este (Maldonado, Rocha, Treinta y Tres, Cerro Largo, Tacuarembó,
          Lavalleja, Canelones [eastern part]).

Tables:

Serie A

 1.Bella Vista             6  2  3  1 11- 6  9  [Paysandú, Paysandú]
 2.Río Negro               6  2  2  2 11- 8  8  [San José, San José]
 3.San Eugenio             6  1  4  1 10- 8  7  [Artigas, Artigas]
 4.Porongos                6  2  1  3  3-13  7  [Trinidad, Flores]

Serie B

 1.Punta del Este          6  3  3  0  9- 2 12  [Punta del Este, Maldonado]
 2.Atenas                  6  3  2  1  9- 6 11  [San Carlos, Maldonado]
 3.Boca Juniors            6  1  2  3  3- 8  5  [Melo, Cerro Largo]
 4.River Plate             6  1  1  4  4- 9  4  [Florida, Florida]

